==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enterocœle
<hw>En"ter*o*c⟦oe⟧le`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'e`nteron</grk> an intestine + <grk>koi^lon</grk> a hollow.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A perivisceral cavity which arises as an
outgrowth or outgrowths from the digestive tract; distinguished from a
<contr>schizoc⟦oe⟧le</contr>, which arises by a splitting of the
mesoblast of the embryo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enterography</ent>⟦br⟧
